# AgToosa Spec Rules
When executing `/agtoosa-spec` or any specification work, follow `Docs/AgToosa_Spec.md` precisely.
**Operating context:** Generated Project Mode — scope specs to **the project/product**; see `Docs/AgToosa_Agent.md` → **Operating Contexts**.
## Key constraints
- Follow the **Plan-Mode Spec Interview Contract** in `Docs/AgToosa_Spec.md` (canonical) plus **Smart Interview Protocol** (`Docs/AgToosa_Agent.md`): research before asking; full flow adaptive cap **8** core questions; `quick` cap **2**; infer before asking; one question at a time with contextual options and a recommended default.
- Always verify dependency versions against live sources — never assume from memory.
- STRIDE threat model is mandatory for every spec (skip only for `quick`).
- Output: a single spec file at `Docs/archived/spec-[story-id].md` with embedded architectural blueprint and threat model.
- **Phase stop:** stop at the approval gate. Do **not** run `/agtoosa-build` automatically. Approval marks readiness only.
- Update `Docs/Master-Plan.md` after the spec is written.
- For `to-issues`: use vertical slices only — each issue must deliver one complete user-facing behaviour change.
- On successful completion, print this line verbatim: `Next: /agtoosa-<command> — <rationale>` plus `SYNC:` pulse (see Lifecycle Next-Step Contract)
